    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Set some <strong>butter </strong>near a warm place to get to room temperature and reserve for easy spreading later on</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/leek-and-sweet-potato-soup-with-cheesy-marmite-toasties/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced leek[s]</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/leek-and-sweet-potato-soup-with-cheesy-marmite-toasties/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the leek[s] soften, peel and chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[1.025L] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.3L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/leek-and-sweet-potato-soup-with-cheesy-marmite-toasties/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek[s] has softened, remove<strong> </strong>1/4 from the pot and set aside for later (this will add extra texture to your soup!)</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and cook over a medium-high heat for 12-15 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/leek-and-sweet-potato-soup-with-cheesy-marmite-toasties/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Spread the <strong>reserved butter </strong>over the top[s] and bottom[s] of the <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong>, then spread your <strong>Marmite </strong>(don't like Marmite? Go easy!) evenly between the inside[s] of the ciabatta[s]</p><p>Sandwich the <strong>grated cheese </strong>between the ciabatta[s] \u2013 these is your <strong>cheesy Marmite sandwich[es]</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/leek-and-sweet-potato-soup-with-cheesy-marmite-toasties/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cheesy Marmite sandwich[es] </strong>and cover with a smaller pan</p><p>Add a heavy weight (e.g. several cans) to the top pan and cook for 2-3 min per side, checking occasionally \u2013 these is your <strong>cheesy Marmite toastie[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/leek-and-sweet-potato-soup-with-cheesy-marmite-toasties/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are done, stir your<strong> soft cheese</strong> through the soup and blitz until smooth with a <strong>(stick) blender</strong></p><p>Stir the<strong> reserved leeks</strong> through the soup and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>leek & potato soup</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of boiled water if the soup is looking a little thick!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/leek-and-sweet-potato-soup-with-cheesy-marmite-toasties/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>cheesy Marmite toastie[s] </strong>into thirds lengthways (soldiers) and serve with the <strong>leek & potato soup</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chives </strong>finely</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>chopped chives</strong> over the soup and drizzle with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
